            <h4>LL07 Frequenty Asked Questions</h4>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-037/">LL07-037 "Chika Takami"</a> to <a href="/card/LL07-045/">LL07-045 "Ruby
                    Kurosawa"</a></h5>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#stand_by">What is the "On Stand-By" state?</a>
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-046/">LL07-046 "Chika Takami"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="046">
                What happens if I <%- skillFormat("⟪ENTER⟫") %> this card with less than three cards in my Deck?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Even if you have less than three cards in your Deck, you can add one Member without Stars to your Hand
                and return the rest to the bottom of your Deck.
                However, even if all of them have no Stars, you cannot take another turn, as the requirement for that
                effect calls for "three cards without Stars" to be shown.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-047/">LL07-047 "Riko Sakurauchi"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="047">
                If I only have one face-up Song card in my Set List, can I flip one face-down Song card face-up?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Yes. The "all your face-up Song cards have the same Attribute" requirement is met in this case, so you
                can flip one face-down Song card face-up.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-048/">LL07-048 "Kanan Matsuura"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="048_same">
                What does "Member with the same Pieces" mean?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                It means a Member who has the exact same number including Piece attributes as another Member.
                The order of Pieces does not matter, so if you <%- skillFormat("⟪ENTER⟫") %>ed a Member
                with <%- skillFormat("[SMILE][PURE], you can ⟪ENTER⟫") %> another Member
                with <%- skillFormat("[PURE][SMILE]") %>.
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="048_bday">
                If I <%- skillFormat("⟪ENTER⟫") %> <a href="/card/LL06-008/">LL06-008 "Mari Ohara"</a> with the Birthday
                Bonus active using this card's Skill, can I <%- skillFormat("⟪ENTER⟫") %> <a href="/card/LL07-051/">LL07-051
                    "Yoshiko Tsushima"</a> from my Hand?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Yes. When the Birthday Bonus is active, the bonus Pieces are added to that card, so in this example, you
                can <%- skillFormat("⟪ENTER⟫") %> <a href="/card/LL07-051/">LL07-051 "Yoshiko Tsushima"</a>.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-049/">LL07-049 "Dia Kurosawa"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="049">
                Can I choose not to draw a card if the designated player decides to let everyone draw cards?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                No. If they decided to have everyone draw cards, all players must draw a card.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-050/">LL07-050 "You Watanabe"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="050">
                When I <%- skillFormat("⟪ENTER⟫ed this card, my Deck was empty. Can I use this Skill to ⟪ENTER⟫") %> the
                card I returned?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Yes. Since it's the only card you can look at from your Deck, you will only be
                to <%- skillFormat("⟪ENTER⟫") %> the card your returned to your Deck.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-052/">LL07-052 "Hanamaru Kunikida"</a></h5>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#more_less">If a Skill's condition says "more/less than", does it also
                    count if you have the same amount?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#join_success_order">What is the order
                    for <%- skillFormat("[Live Join] / [Live Success]") %> Skills?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="052">
                In a two-player match, both players have the same amount of cards in their Hand. What happens in case
                there are two or more of this Member participating in a <%- skillFormat("⟪LIVE⟫") %>?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                The first <span class="redtext">"Hanamaru"</span>'s Skill will result in the player drawing a card.
                After that, when the Skills of the other <span class="redtext">"Hanamaru"</span> cards are resolved, the
                player will have more cards in their Hand than the other player, so the cards
                will <%- skillFormat("gain +[ALL]") %>.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-053/">LL07-053 "Mari Ohara"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="053_hand">
                If a Member doesn't
                have <%- skillFormat("[ALL], but has a Skill such as [Live Join] that allows them to gain [ALL], can I use this card's Skill to ⟪ENTER⟫") %>
                them?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                No. Skills such
                as <%- skillFormat("[Live Join] will only be resolved at that time, so when the card is still in your Hand, it does not have [ALL]") %>
                .
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="053_idolize">
                The Member
                I <%- skillFormat("⟪ENTER⟫ed using this card's Skill has a [Special Practice] Skill, and after being Idolized, they have three or more [ALL]") %>
                . Can I draw three cards in this case?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Yes.
                This <%- skillFormat("[Entry] Skill counts the number of Pieces after the Member was ⟪ENTER⟫ed. If a Member is Idolized through a [Special Practice] Skill, [Idolized (Piece Bonus)] will be active when the card appears on the Stage, so including those, the Member has three or more [ALL]") %>
                and the requirement is met.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-055/">LL07-055 "Kinmirai Happy End"</a></h5>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#stand_by">What is the "On Stand-By" state?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#flip_before_skills">Between flipping over a new Song card from the Set
                    List and the <%- skillFormat("[Live Success]") %> Skills, which one should go first?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="055_end">
                With
                this <%- skillFormat("⟪LIVE⟫, I've reached the Live Points target. If the Skill Requirement is met, can I still perform another ⟪LIVE⟫?") %>
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                No. When they reach the Live Points target, the winner is removed from the rest of the match, so they
                cannot perform a <%- skillFormat("⟪LIVE⟫") %>.
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="055_other">
                What happens if non-<span class="redtext">"CYaRon!"</span> Members are participating in
                this <%- skillFormat("⟪LIVE⟫") %>?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                As long as <span class="redtext">"Chika"</span>, <span class="redtext">"You"</span> and <span
                        class="redtext">"Ruby"</span> have joined this <%- skillFormat("⟪LIVE⟫") %>, the Skill can be
                used no matter what other Members are participating.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-056M/">LL07-056 "GALAXY HidE and SeeK"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="056_noall">
                <a href="/card/LL05-053/">LL05-053 "Mari Ohara"</a> is joining
                a <%- skillFormat("⟪LIVE⟫ with this Song card while this card's Skill requirement is met. There are also members with [SMILE], [PURE] and [COOL]") %>
                . Will the <span class="redtext">"Mari"</span> card
                gain <%- skillFormat("+[ALL] from it's [Live Join]") %> Skill?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                No. The Skill of this Song card changes
                all <%- skillFormat("[SMILE][PURE][COOL] of the Members joining this ⟪LIVE⟫ into [ALL] before [Live Join]") %>
                Skills are resolved. That means that in this case, <span class="redtext">"Mari"</span> does not
                gain <%- skillFormat("+[ALL]") %>.
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="056_later">
                A member who joined
                a <%- skillFormat("⟪LIVE⟫ with this Song card gained +[SMILE] through a [Live Join] Skill. If the requirement for this card's Skill is met, does that Piece also become [ALL]") %>
                ?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Yes. Pieces gained through Skills become <%- skillFormat("[ALL]") %>, too.
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="056_other">
                What happens if non-<span class="redtext">"AZALEA"</span> Members are participating in
                this <%- skillFormat("⟪LIVE⟫") %>?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                As long as <span class="redtext">"Kanan"</span>, <span class="redtext">"Dia"</span> and <span
                        class="redtext">"Hanamaru"</span> have joined this <%- skillFormat("⟪LIVE⟫") %>, the Skill can
                be used no matter what other Members are participating.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-057/">LL07-057 "Kowareyasuki"</a></h5>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#join_success_order">What is the order
                    for <%- skillFormat("[Live Join] / [Live Success]") %> Skills?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#flip_before_skills">Between flipping over a new Song card from the Set
